parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right-side saddlebag latch can cause the lid to open while riding, potentially leading to accidents or hazards to the rider and other vehicles.
symptoms: The right-side saddlebag lid pops open
the latch is worn or broken
the lid does not close properly
the contents of the saddlebag are lost or scattered on the road
the rider experiences a sensation of rear steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden engine stalling can cause the motorcycle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or crashes, especially when traveling at high speeds or navigating curves.
symptoms: The engine stalls suddenly
often when downshifting or pausing during a shift
and may require the rider to restart the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch cable failure can cause the motorcycle to lose control, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: The clutch cable snaps or breaks
causing the clutch to stick or fail to disengage
and may result in the motorcycle stalling or lurching uncontrollably.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning fuel injection system can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or crashes, especially when navigating curves or traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
often when the throttle position is abruptly changed
and may require the rider to restart the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure due to Water Ingress
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause critical safety features such as turn signals and hazard lights to malfunction, leading to increased risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Cruise control malfunctions
hazard warning lights blink erratically
turn signals cease to function
electrical system acts strangely when the motorcycle is exposed to water.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into electrical components can cause corrosion and damage, leading to electrical system failures, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Electrical system malfunctions
turn signals and hazard lights fail to function
cruise control malfunctions
strange electrical behavior when the motorcycle is exposed to water.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling without warning can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Engine stalls without warning
vehicle can be restarted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the saddlebag latch mechanism can cause the saddlebag to fly open while traveling, potentially startling the rider and leading to a crash. Additionally, loose contents from the bag can cause crashes or accidents for other vehicles or riders following behind.
symptoms: The saddlebag latch mechanism is grinding or worn
the hoop has worn into the latch
the aluminum part is worn
the saddlebag is subject to flying open while traveling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inconsistent operation of self-canceling turn signals can lead to a lack of indication to other drivers, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when the motorcycle is stationary or turning.
symptoms: Turn signals cancel prematurely
often after as few as three flashes
and do not consistently follow the manufacturer's specified cancellation criteria
such as speed
distance
and duration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of rear lights can reduce the motorcycle's visibility to other drivers, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: All rear lights fail
including brake lights and turn signals
while driving at low speeds.
